-third,There needs to be more action.  Like on the way home from the bar in the begining he is drunk and really loses his mind.  A couple of (Agents) created by the enemy highjacks his car and brings him to thier base to expirement on him.  Like i said in the other thread.  They give him his fantasy powers.  Using these he becomes smart and escapes.  Then the enemy (agents) are searching for him.  ( The main theme is that usually he is the hunter, the assasin, but now he is the hunted.)  Having no place to stay he visits his uncle then finding out the history of his family, he becomes mad.  Stuff happens he gets in a few fights, and is chased around.  The girl teams up with him, so he can get his life back and be normal.  If she is a scientist then she can bring him back to normal.  Then well i am not sure what happens next.  Tell me what u think. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ufalcondelta.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FalconDelta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/8/01 7:19:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=342.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hipolymer.virtualave.net/images/Delta.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ok lets work out the kinks</span><hr size=1> I think that the the 'hunter - hunted' theme is a bit overused as a theme I was hoping to have a more unique edge. We might use it as one of the sub-polts for i think it has relevence but as far as the entire theme goes i think we should forego it. I think identity crisis would be a better theme, he thinks he is one person but realizes after talking to his uncle that his past is much larger than even he himself realizes. This is troublesome and disorenting for him. As far as drinking and going mad, this isnt an angle we should take. Its not really feasible that an assasin would degrade himself to this sort of level. Its just, i dunno, i dont like it too much. He'd be crap as an assasin if he were always drinking and mad. It needs to be a sort of internal conflict, he is trying to bring light to the darkness that resides in his soul.<br>
<br>
I did see anit trust and no i wasnt thinking about it at the time when i concieved the relationship between the girl and the main character. I agree it needs to be reworked a bit. I was inbetween having her as a double agent and simply unaware of what is going on. I think a love story is important to the message of the text, however. I wanted to show that even though there is an apparent hate for the world that love and hate can be simultaniously found.<br>
<br>
I think I should scratch the double agent idea. I'm beginning to think of it as a lemon. Maybe it would be better if she were some how connected with the family, but unaware of what was going on. How about this, she was the daughter of a rival syndicate and in a raid by the Pendant special team she is abducted. Very young she does not really remember her parents. The Pendants set her up with the main characters Uncle who essentially acts as her guardian, she trains with the Pendants for a while but she is loyal to the uncle. She doesnt remember her parents and she loves the main characters uncle like her own father. When he is assasinated (by the pendants) she wants revenge. It happens that she and the main character are after the same thing. Although there is an initial animosity they find themselves joining forces then falling for each other near the end. That way we can have a subtle love story, its a sub-plot not the major plot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uchildprodigy11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>childprodigy11</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/10/01 3:36:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=342.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Team of fantasy/action writers</span><hr size=1> the planet that he lives on could be sorta like a waste land where buisness groups like the mafia are in control.<br>
(sorry it took me so long)<br>
tell me if this you have already talked about this because I don't have time right now to read all of falcons posts. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uchildprodigy11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>childprodigy11</A> at: 10/11/01 12:15:54 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ulordgabriel3.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Gabriel 3</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/11/01 3:54:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=342.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/dogfuchow/pie.jpg height=120 width=120></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Team of fantasy/action writers</span><hr size=1> how about this: Anyone read the Crucible? Try a group of people, who have been powerless their entire life, and have tons of emotional baggage, suddenly coming into unbelievable (god-like) powers. And then make THEM your villains. Power is one of the most dangerous features any antagonist can have, and when one has never had power before, abuse of power is thrice as deadly.<br>
<br>
You can definitely base this around scifi themes. I know, because several of my unpublished works are futuristic and logically scientific. You can do pretty much anything with an enormous leeway on physics.<br>
<br>
Just a suggestion. I've been thinking about a balance of power theme for a while, and if you don't want to use this idea, I'll gladly take over. The balance of power theme? Your &quot;villains,&quot; the people who come into power, have a rivalry between each other, due to natural varying levels of aggression (this is proven psychiatry, THE main reason for every argument you've ever had with someone. Now imagine being in an argument with someone, and you have the power to completely massacre the opposition). Their rivalry will most certainly become devastatingly catastrophic.<br>
<br>
Heh. Like I said, you can use this idea if you want. If not, I'll use it, since I've been developing the plot for almost four years now.<br>
<br>
