<br>
I was referring to how people react to gain power, which is what happened during the Red Scare <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> and</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the Salem Witch Trials. They used the power given to them by simply being there as a witness to turn people against each other, and betray friends who defy them, and cast vengeance on those who were in their way. And murder, if needed.<br>
<br>
Just a way to look at things when involved in the matters. Don't make the villains antagonists because they can kill people, make them antagonists because they can turn others against you, ruin your ability to return to society, and then kill you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><b>Gaealord Gabriel Angelo Maokai III</b>
